   <titleInfo>
      <title>Letter, John Watkins in Knoxville, Tenn. to Sarah Probert in Pittsfield, Ohio, 1863 November 2</title>
   </titleInfo>
   <abstract>In this letter, dated November 2, 1863, from John Watkins in Knoxville, Tenn., to Sarah Probert in Pittsfield, Ohio, Watkins writes about the jobs he has had to do and describes the cabins that he and the other soldiers have been building for winter accomodation. He stresses that he and the 19th Ohio Battery have yet to see any action. He also discusses general news from Ohio.</abstract>
